%% User Task Flow — Floor
%% End-to-end sequence: prompt composition through implementation and shutdown.
%% Generated by architecture health check. Do not edit manually.

sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Developer
    participant F as floor.py
    participant TC as task_counter.py
    participant CC as check_cdocs.py
    participant CA as Claude (prompting)
    participant CI as Claude Code (impl)
    participant S as shutdown.py
    participant CM as check_manifest.py
    participant CV as check_cdoc_coverage.py

    Note over U,F: Phase 1 — Prompt composition

    U->>F: python project_management/scripts/floor.py "task description"
    F->>TC: subprocess read
    TC-->>F: counter value

    alt Counter >= 10
        F-->>U: Architecture check required — run architecture-check.md
    else Counter < 10
        F->>CC: subprocess (staleness report)
        CC-->>F: stale/fresh per cdoc
        F->>F: read prompting.md, status.md
        F->>F: assemble prompt, write .floor_session.json
        F->>CA: exec claude CLI with assembled prompt

        CA->>U: draft task prompt (iterates until satisfied)
        CA->>CA: write final prompt to prompts/implement-this.md
        CA->>CA: record status_item_id in .floor_session.json (if matched)
    end

    Note over U,CI: Phase 2 — Implementation

    U->>CI: open Claude Code session, say "implement"
    CI->>CI: read CLAUDE.md → read prompts/implement-this.md
    CI->>CI: read manifest.md, relevant cdocs, standards
    CI->>U: present plan
    U->>CI: approve / iterate
    CI->>CI: implement task

    Note over U,S: Phase 3 — Shutdown & doc sync

    U->>CI: confirm task complete
    CI->>S: python project_management/scripts/shutdown.py
    S->>CV: subprocess → coverage report
    S->>CM: subprocess → manifest audit
    S->>CC: subprocess → staleness report
    S->>TC: subprocess increment
    S->>S: delete .floor_session.json
    S-->>CI: structured results (markdown)

    CI->>CI: read cdoc.md
    CI->>CI: update stale cdocs, fix manifest gaps, update status
    CI-->>U: remind to git commit
